# Documentation
# This is a KAPE Compound Module, and Compound Module references resolve recursively -
# MFTECmd.mkape and RegRipper.mkape are themselves stock Compound Modules referencing
# further leaf modules (confirmed working via a direct nested-resolution test).
# See Modules\CompoundModuleGuide.guide in the KAPE install for the mechanism itself.
#
# Deliberately NOT using:
# - PowerShell_SrumECmd_SRUM-RepairAndParse.mkape: would auto-repair a dirty SRUDB.dat,
#   but its underlying SRUM-Repair.ps1 dismisses an esentutl /p GUI warning dialog via
#   SendKeys/AppActivate, which can hang indefinitely in an unattended/non-interactive
#   run if the popup can't be found/activated. If a future collection's SRUM database
#   is dirty, repair it manually (esentutl /r then /p) and re-run SrumECmd in isolation.
# - PowerShell_MFTECmd_J-MFTParsing.mkape: cross-references $MFT and $J to populate
#   ParentPath in the USN output (a genuinely better result), but its search is
#   hardcoded to a file literally named "$J" - Velociraptor collects the USN journal as
#   "$UsnJrnl%3A$J", so this script would never find it. MFTECmd.mkape's own $J
#   sub-module already accounts for the Velociraptor naming in its FileMask.
